FeatureType.Name: fifao:LME
FeatureType.Title: The 66 Large Marine Ecosystems of the World
FeatureType.Abstract: Since 1984, the NOAA Fisheries Service's Large Marine Ecosystems (LME) Program has been engaged in the development and implementation of an ecosystem-based approach to support assessment and management of marine resources and habitats. Five linked program modules have been developed for introducing the LME approach: productivity, fish and fisheries, pollution and ecosystem health, socioeconomics, and governance. Taken together, these modules provide time-series measurements used to support actions for the recovery, sustainability, and management of marine resources and habitats. A global effort is underway by NOAA in partnership with the World Conservation Union (IUCN), the UN's Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission (IOC), and other UN agencies to improve the long-term sustainability of resources and environments of the world's 66 LMEs and linked watersheds. Scientific and technical assistance is provided to developing countries committed to policies and actions for eliminating transboundary environmental and resource-use practices that lead to serious degradation of coastal environments and their linked watersheds, and to losses in biodiversity and food security.

FeatureType.Name: vme:vme_indicator_fishing
FeatureType.Title: vme_indicator_fishing
FeatureType.Abstract:
This Indicator gives surface and underlying percentages calculated by difference of the RFMO area, on a yearly basis. Surfaces given are: RFMO, Total surface of VME closure (VME), Total surface of Other Access regulated Areas (OARA) and the sum VME+OARA. Percentages are then given. % of area over total RFMO area, In/Out VME closures (P_IN_VME/P_OUT_VME), In/Out OARAs (P_IN_OARA/P_OUT_OARA), and In/Out VME closures+OARA as % indicator of closed/regulated areas vs. Areas fully open to fishing activity (not closed or without any regulation)
The structure of the indicator is as follows:
OWNER = RFMO YEAR = Year considered SURF_RFMO = Surface of RFMO convention area SURF_VME = Total Surface of VME closures SURF_OARA = Total Surface of Other access regulated areas (OARAs) SURF_ALL = Total surface of VME closures + OARAs P_IN_VME = Percent of VME closures over the total RFMO area (same as previous computation) P_OUT_VME = Percent of areas different from VME closures over the total RFMO area (same as previous computation) P_IN_OARA = Percent of OARAs over the total RFMO area (same as previous computation) P_OUT_OARA = Percent of areas different from OARAs over the total RFMO area (same as previous computation) P_IN_ALL = Percent VME closures + OARAS over the total RFMO area ~ Closed/Regulated areas P_OUT_ALL = Percent of areas not being VME closures or OARAS over the total RFMO area ~ Areas fully open to fishing activity (not closed or without any regulation)
